**McKesson Corporation: A Leading Player in the Healthcare Wholesaling Industry**

As ranked 9th in the Fortune 2024 list, McKesson Corporation continues to demonstrate its resilience and adaptability in the ever-evolving healthcare landscape. With a rich history and a strong presence in the healthcare sector, McKesson has solidified its position as a leading wholesaler of healthcare products.

Headquartered in Irving, Texas, McKesson is a public company with a market value of $75,007 million as of July 15, 2024. The company's fiscal year, which ended on March 31, 2024, saw revenues of $276,711 million, representing a modest 4.8% increase from the previous year. More notable, however, was the significant surge in profits, which grew by 219.6% to $3,560 million. This substantial increase in profitability is a testament to the company's ability to navigate the complexities of the healthcare industry and capitalize on emerging opportunities.

Under the leadership of CEO Brian S. Tyler, McKesson has continued to execute its strategic vision, leveraging its extensive network and expertise to deliver value to its customers and stakeholders. With a workforce of approximately 48,000 employees, the company is well-positioned to drive growth and innovation in the healthcare sector.

McKesson's commitment to delivering high-quality healthcare products and services has earned it a reputation as a trusted partner in the industry. As a global company, McKesson is listed on the Global 500, recognizing its significant presence and influence in the international market.

While McKesson did not experience any changes in its ranking, it remains a stalwart member of the Fortune 500, a testament to its enduring strength and stability. The company's market capitalization has also seen a notable increase, from $70,546.5 million on March 28, 2024, to $75,007 million on July 15, 2024.

As the healthcare industry continues to evolve, McKesson is poised to remain a key player, leveraging its expertise and resources to drive growth and innovation. With a strong leadership team and a proven track record of success, McKesson is well-positioned to navigate the complexities of the healthcare sector and deliver value to its stakeholders.

For more information on McKesson Corporation, please visit their website at https://www.mckesson.com.